{
  "cells": [
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "# Absolute Sum Minimization Experiment\n",
        "\n",
        "**Goal:** Minimize sums of absolute polynomials over $p$-adic fields:\n",
        "$$L(x) = |f_1(x)| + |f_2(x)| + \\cdots + |f_n(x)|$$\n",
        "where $f_1, \\ldots, f_n$ are polynomials with random fixed coefficients, and $x \\in \\mathbb{Q}_p^d$.\n",
        "\n",
        "We compare multiple optimization methods: **Random**, **Greedy**, **MCTS-50**, **MCTS-100**, and **MCTS-200**."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "include(\"../../../src/NAML.jl\")\n",
        "include(\"../util.jl\")\n",
        "include(\"util.jl\")\n",
        "\n",
        "using Oscar\n",
        "using .NAML\n",
        "using Printf"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## 1. Configuration\n",
        "\n",
        "Set the experiment parameters here."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "# Field configuration\n",
        "PRIME = 2\n",
        "PREC = 20\n",
        "K = PadicField(PRIME, PREC)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Problem configuration\n",
        "NUM_POLYS = 2            # Number of polynomials in the sum\n",
        "NUM_VARS = 1             # Number of variables (dimension)\n",
        "POLY_DEGREE = 1          # Degree of each polynomial (1=linear, 2=quadratic)\n",
        "OPT_DEGREE = 2           # Optimization degree for children()\n",
        "N_EPOCHS = 20            # Optimization epochs per optimizer\n",
        "\n",
        "println(\"Configuration:\")\n",
        "println(\"  Prime: $PRIME\")\n",
        "println(\"  Precision: $PREC\")\n",
        "println(\"  Number of polynomials: $NUM_POLYS\")\n",
        "println(\"  Variables (dimension): $NUM_VARS\")\n",
        "println(\"  Polynomial degree: $POLY_DEGREE\")\n",
        "println(\"  Optimization degree: $OPT_DEGREE\")\n",
        "println(\"  Epochs: $N_EPOCHS\")"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## 2. Generate Random Problem\n",
        "\n",
        "Generate random polynomials $f_1, \\ldots, f_n$ with fixed coefficients."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "# Generate random absolute sum minimization problem\n",
        "loss = generate_random_absolute_sum_problem(PRIME, PREC, NUM_POLYS, NUM_VARS, POLY_DEGREE)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Initial parameters at Gauss point\n",
        "initial_param = generate_initial_point(NUM_VARS, K)\n",
        "initial_loss = loss.eval([initial_param])[1]\n",
        "\n",
        "println(\"Generated $NUM_POLYS random polynomials in $NUM_VARS variable(s)\")\n",
        "println(\"Initial parameter: center at (1, ..., 1), radius 0\")\n",
        "println(\"Initial loss: $initial_loss\")\n",
        "println(\"  |initial_loss| = \", Float64(initial_loss))"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## 3. Define Optimizers\n",
        "\n",
        "We compare several optimization strategies with different hyperparameters."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "optimizer_defs = [\n",
        "    (name=\"Random\",\n",
        "     init=(p, l) -> NAML.random_descent_init(p, l, 1, (false, OPT_DEGREE))),\n",
        "    \n",
        "    (name=\"Greedy\",\n",
        "     init=(p, l) -> NAML.greedy_descent_init(p, l, 1, (false, OPT_DEGREE))),\n",
        "    \n",
        "    (name=\"MCTS-50\",\n",
        "     init=(p, l) -> NAML.mcts_descent_init(p, l,\n",
        "         NAML.MCTSConfig(num_simulations=50, exploration_constant=1.41,\n",
        "                         selection_mode=NAML.BestValue, degree=OPT_DEGREE))),\n",
        "    \n",
        "    (name=\"MCTS-100\",\n",
        "     init=(p, l) -> NAML.mcts_descent_init(p, l,\n",
        "         NAML.MCTSConfig(num_simulations=100, exploration_constant=1.41,\n",
        "                         selection_mode=NAML.BestValue, degree=OPT_DEGREE))),\n",
        "    \n",
        "    (name=\"MCTS-200\",\n",
        "     init=(p, l) -> NAML.mcts_descent_init(p, l,\n",
        "         NAML.MCTSConfig(num_simulations=200, exploration_constant=1.41,\n",
        "                         selection_mode=NAML.BestValue, degree=OPT_DEGREE))),\n",
        "]\n",
        "\n",
        "println(\"Optimizers to compare:\")\n",
        "for od in optimizer_defs\n",
        "    println(\"  - \$(od.name)\")\n",
        "end"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## 4. Run Experiments\n",
        "\n",
        "Run each optimizer and record loss trajectories."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "# Store results: name => (losses, time, final_param)\n",
        "results = Dict{String, Any}()\n",
        "\n",
        "for od in optimizer_defs\n",
        "    println(\"\\nRunning \$(od.name)...\")\n",
        "    \n",
        "    optim = od.init(initial_param, loss)\n",
        "    losses = Float64[]\n",
        "    \n",
        "    t_start = time()\n",
        "    for epoch in 1:N_EPOCHS\n",
        "        current_loss = NAML.eval_loss(optim)\n",
        "        push!(losses, current_loss)\n",
        "        NAML.step!(optim)\n",
        "    end\n",
        "    final_loss = NAML.eval_loss(optim)\n",
        "    push!(losses, final_loss)\n",
        "    elapsed = time() - t_start\n",
        "    \n",
        "    results[od.name] = Dict(\n",
        "        \"losses\" => losses,\n",
        "        \"time\" => elapsed,\n",
        "        \"final_loss\" => final_loss,\n",
        "        \"final_param\" => optim.param,\n",
        "    )\n",
        "    \n",
        "    improvement = (initial_loss > 0) ? (initial_loss - final_loss) / initial_loss * 100 : 0.0\n",
        "    @printf(\"  %s: final_loss = %.6e, improvement = %.1f%%, time = %.2fs\\n\",\n",
        "            od.name, final_loss, improvement, elapsed)\n",
        "end\n",
        "\n",
        "println(\"\\nAll optimizers finished.\")"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## 5. Summary Table"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "println(\"\\nSUMMARY\")\n",
        "println(\"=\"^70)\n",
        "println(\"Problem: \$(PRIME)-adic, \$(NUM_POLYS) polynomials, \$(NUM_VARS) var(s), degree \$(POLY_DEGREE), \$(N_EPOCHS) epochs\")\n",
        "println(\"Initial loss: $initial_loss\")\n",
        "println()\n",
        "@printf(\"%-15s %15s %12s %12s\\n\", \"Optimizer\", \"Final Loss\", \"Improv %\", \"Time (s)\")\n",
        "println(\"-\"^55)\n",
        "\n",
        "for od in optimizer_defs\n",
        "    r = results[od.name]\n",
        "    improv = (initial_loss > 0) ? (initial_loss - r[\"final_loss\"]) / initial_loss * 100 : 0.0\n",
        "    @printf(\"%-15s %15.6e %11.1f%% %12.2f\\n\",\n",
        "            od.name, r[\"final_loss\"], improv, r[\"time\"])\n",
        "end\n",
        "\n",
        "# Find best\n",
        "best_name = \"\"\n",
        "best_loss = Inf\n",
        "for od in optimizer_defs\n",
        "    if results[od.name][\"final_loss\"] < best_loss\n",
        "        best_loss = results[od.name][\"final_loss\"]\n",
        "        best_name = od.name\n",
        "    end\n",
        "end\n",
        "println(\"\\nBest optimizer: $best_name (loss = $best_loss)\")"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## 6. Loss Trajectories\n",
        "\n",
        "Display the loss over epochs for each optimizer."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "# Print loss trajectories as text\n",
        "println(\"\\nLoss trajectories (selected epochs):\")\n",
        "println()\n",
        "\n",
        "# Header\n",
        "header = @sprintf(\"%-8s\", \"Epoch\")\n",
        "for od in optimizer_defs\n",
        "    header *= @sprintf(\" %15s\", od.name)\n",
        "end\n",
        "println(header)\n",
        "println(\"-\"^(8 + 16 * length(optimizer_defs)))\n",
        "\n",
        "# Print selected epochs\n",
        "epochs_to_show = unique(vcat([1, 2, 3, 5, 10], collect(10:10:N_EPOCHS), [N_EPOCHS, N_EPOCHS+1]))\n",
        "epochs_to_show = filter(e -> e <= N_EPOCHS + 1, sort(epochs_to_show))\n",
        "\n",
        "for epoch in epochs_to_show\n",
        "    label = epoch <= N_EPOCHS ? string(epoch) : \"final\"\n",
        "    row = @sprintf(\"%-8s\", label)\n",
        "    for od in optimizer_defs\n",
        "        losses = results[od.name][\"losses\"]\n",
        "        if epoch <= length(losses)\n",
        "            row *= @sprintf(\" %15.6e\", losses[epoch])\n",
        "        end\n",
        "    end\n",
        "    println(row)\n",
        "end"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## 7. Optimal Point\n",
        "\n",
        "Inspect the optimal point found by the best optimizer."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "println(\"Optimal point ($best_name):\")\n",
        "println()\n",
        "\n",
        "best_param = results[best_name][\"final_param\"]\n",
        "best_center = NAML.center(best_param)\n",
        "best_radius = NAML.radius(best_param)\n",
        "\n",
        "for (i, x) in enumerate(best_center)\n",
        "    x_abs = Float64(abs(x))\n",
        "    r = best_radius[i]\n",
        "    @printf(\"  x%d: |x%d| = %.6e, radius = %d\\n\", i, i, x_abs, r)\n",
        "end\n",
        "\n",
        "println(\"\\nFinal loss at this point: \", best_loss)"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## 8. Multi-Configuration Sweep\n",
        "\n",
        "Run the experiment across multiple configurations to see how performance varies\n",
        "with problem parameters."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "# Sweep over different problem sizes\n",
        "sweep_configs = [\n",
        "    (prime=2, prec=20, num_polys=2, num_vars=1, degree=1, opt_degree=2),\n",
        "    (prime=2, prec=20, num_polys=2, num_vars=1, degree=2, opt_degree=2),\n",
        "    (prime=2, prec=20, num_polys=3, num_vars=2, degree=1, opt_degree=2),\n",
        "    (prime=3, prec=15, num_polys=2, num_vars=1, degree=1, opt_degree=2),\n",
        "]\n",
        "\n",
        "SWEEP_EPOCHS = 15\n",
        "\n",
        "sweep_results = []\n",
        "\n",
        "for cfg in sweep_configs\n",
        "    println(\"\\nRunning: p=\$(cfg.prime), \$(cfg.num_polys) polys, \$(cfg.num_vars) vars, deg=\$(cfg.degree)\")\n",
        "    \n",
        "    Ks = PadicField(cfg.prime, cfg.prec)\n",
        "    l = generate_random_absolute_sum_problem(cfg.prime, cfg.prec, cfg.num_polys, cfg.num_vars, cfg.degree)\n",
        "    p0 = generate_initial_point(cfg.num_vars, Ks)\n",
        "    l0 = l.eval([p0])[1]\n",
        "    \n",
        "    cfg_results = Dict(\"config\" => cfg, \"initial_loss\" => l0, \"optimizers\" => Dict())\n",
        "    \n",
        "    for od in optimizer_defs\n",
        "        try\n",
        "            opt = od.init(p0, l)\n",
        "            t0 = time()\n",
        "            for e in 1:SWEEP_EPOCHS\n",
        "                NAML.step!(opt)\n",
        "            end\n",
        "            fl = NAML.eval_loss(opt)\n",
        "            dt = time() - t0\n",
        "            improv = (l0 > 0) ? (l0 - fl) / l0 * 100 : 0.0\n",
        "            cfg_results[\"optimizers\"][od.name] = Dict(\n",
        "                \"final_loss\" => fl, \"time\" => dt, \"improvement\" => improv\n",
        "            )\n",
        "            @printf(\"  %-15s final=%.6e  improv=%.1f%%  time=%.2fs\\n\", od.name, fl, improv, dt)\n",
        "        catch e\n",
        "            println(\"  \$(od.name): ERROR - $e\")\n",
        "            cfg_results[\"optimizers\"][od.name] = Dict(\"error\" => string(e))\n",
        "        end\n",
        "    end\n",
        "    \n",
        "    push!(sweep_results, cfg_results)\n",
        "end\n",
        "\n",
        "println(\"\\nSweep complete.\")"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## 9. Sweep Summary Table"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "println(\"\\nSWEEP SUMMARY\")\n",
        "println(\"=\"^90)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Header\n",
        "header = @sprintf(\"%-30s\", \"Config\")\n",
        "for od in optimizer_defs\n",
        "    header *= @sprintf(\" %12s\", od.name)\n",
        "end\n",
        "println(header)\n",
        "println(\"-\"^(30 + 13 * length(optimizer_defs)))\n",
        "\n",
        "for sr in sweep_results\n",
        "    cfg = sr[\"config\"]\n",
        "    label = \"p=\$(cfg.prime) \$(cfg.num_polys)p \$(cfg.num_vars)v d=\$(cfg.degree)\"\n",
        "    row = @sprintf(\"%-30s\", label)\n",
        "    \n",
        "    for od in optimizer_defs\n",
        "        if haskey(sr[\"optimizers\"], od.name)\n",
        "            or = sr[\"optimizers\"][od.name]\n",
        "            if haskey(or, \"error\")\n",
        "                row *= @sprintf(\" %12s\", \"ERR\")\n",
        "            else\n",
        "                row *= @sprintf(\" %12.4e\", or[\"final_loss\"])\n",
        "            end\n",
        "        else\n",
        "            row *= @sprintf(\" %12s\", \"---\")\n",
        "        end\n",
        "    end\n",
        "    println(row)\n",
        "end\n",
        "\n",
        "println(\"\\n(All values are final loss after $SWEEP_EPOCHS epochs)\")"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## Summary\n",
        "\n",
        "This notebook demonstrates absolute sum minimization over $p$-adic fields using various\n",
        "optimization methods from the NAML library.\n",
        "\n",
        "**Key findings:**\n",
        "- Random descent provides a baseline for comparison\n",
        "- Greedy descent is fast but may get stuck in local minima\n",
        "- MCTS methods explore the space more thoroughly\n",
        "- Increasing MCTS simulations generally improves results at the cost of computation time\n",
        "\n",
        "**To reproduce at scale:** Use `run_experiments.jl` with `--save` to generate JSON results,\n",
        "then `generate_tables.jl` to produce a unified LaTeX document with all tables."
      ]
    }
  ],
